
Added:
- 3 firewalls: edge, LB->App, App->DB (least privilege)
- HTTPS (SSL cert): encrypt/authenticate traffic
- Monitoring clients: collect metrics/logs for LB, App, DB

Monitoring QPS:
- Use Nginx/HAProxy/app metrics; dashboard + alerts

Issues:
- LB TLS termination only -> plaintext inside unless re-encrypted
- Single write MySQL -> write bottleneck & failover risk
- Same components on all servers -> contention & larger blast radiusTalking points (1–2 minutes):

Firewalls: perimeter to block unwanted access, host-level to limit lateral movement, DB firewall to restrict 3306.
HTTPS: encrypts traffic; mention Let's Encrypt for certs.
Monitoring: collectors (Prometheus node_exporter or Sumo agent) on every host; use exporters or log shippers.
QPS monitoring quick note: use Nginx stub_status or HAProxy stats + Prometheus to compute request rate (QPS).
Screenshot_URL: https://imgur.com/REPLACE_TASK2User (browser)
